 16class ValidatorModelABC(ABC):
 17
 18    def __init__(
 19        self,
 20        data_models_context: DataModelsContext,
 21        report_list: ModelListReport,
 22        type_class: Type[SpModelABC],
 23        **kwargs: Dict[str, Any],
 24    ):
 25        # SETUP
 26        self._data_models_context = data_models_context
 27        self._report_list = report_list
 28        self._type_class = type_class
 29
 30        # UNPACK DATA
 31        self._data_model = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(self._type_class)
 32        self._filename = self._data_model.filename if self._data_model else "Unknown"
 33        self._dataframe = (
 34            self._data_model.data_loader_model.df_data.copy()
 35            if self._data_model
 36            else pd.DataFrame({})
 37        )
 38        self.TITLES_INFO = self._data_models_context.config.get_verify_names()
 39
 40        # LIST OF ERRORS AND WARNINGS
 41        self._errors: List[str] = []
 42        self._warnings: List[str] = []

 49    def check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
 50        self,
 51        required_columns: Dict[str, List[str]],
 52        model_dataframes: Dict[str, pd.DataFrame],
 53    ) -> List[str]:
 54        """
 55        Check if required columns exist in the provided dataframes for different models.
 56        :param required_columns: A dictionary where keys are model names and values are lists of required column names.
 57        :param model_dataframes: A dictionary where keys are model names and values are their corresponding dataframes.
 58        :return: A list of error messages for missing columns.
 59        """
 60        errors = []
 61
 62        # Check if columns exist
 63        for model_name, columns in required_columns.items():
 64            dataframe = model_dataframes[model_name]
 65            if dataframe is not None:
 66                for column in columns:
 67                    exists_column, error_msg = self.column_exists(
 68                        dataframe, model_name, column
 69                    )
 70                    if not exists_column:
 71                        errors.append(error_msg)
 72
 73        return errors
 74
 75    # Create static method to check if column exists
 76    def column_exists(self, dataframe, filename, column) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
 77
 78        # How use: To use this method, you can call it directly with the dataframe and column name.
 79        # For example:
 80        # exists, msg_error_column = ValidatorModelABC.column_exists(dataframe, filename, column
 81        exists, msg_error_column = column_exists(dataframe, filename, column)
 82        return exists, msg_error_column
 83
 84    def _column_exists(self, column: str) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
 85        exists, msg_error_column = column_exists(
 86            self._dataframe, self._filename, column
 87        )
 88        return exists, msg_error_column
 89
 90    def _column_exists_dataframe(self, dataframe, column: str) -> Tuple[bool, str]:
 91        exists, msg_error_column = column_exists(dataframe, self._filename, column)
 92        return exists, msg_error_column

 94    def _check_text_length(
 95        self, column: str, max_len: int
 96    ) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 97        """Helper function to validate text length in a column."""
 98        warnings = []
 99        __, warnings_text_length = check_text_length(
100            dataframe=self._dataframe,
101            file_name=self._filename,
102            column=column,
103            max_length=max_len,
104        )
105        warnings.extend(warnings_text_length)
106        return [], warnings

109        pass

116    def build_reports(self, validations):
117        for func, report_key in validations:
118            try:
119                errors, warnings = func()
120                if errors or warnings:
121                    self._report_list.extend(
122                        self.TITLES_INFO[report_key], errors=errors, warnings=warnings
123                    )
124                self._errors.extend(errors)
125                self._warnings.extend(warnings)
126            except Exception as e:
127                self._report_list.extend(
128                    self.TITLES_INFO[report_key],
129                    errors=[
130                        f"Exception validation in file during {func.__name__}: {str(e)}"
131                    ],
132                    warnings=[],
133                )

 46    def validate_html_in_descriptions(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 47        warnings = []
 48        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name
 49        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 50        if not exists_column:
 51            return [msg_error_column], []
 52        for index, row in self._dataframe.iterrows():
 53            if re.search("<.*?>", str(row[column])):
 54                index = int(str(index))
 55                warnings.append(
 56                    f"{self._filename}, linha {index + 2}: Coluna '{column}' não pode conter código HTML."
 57                )
 58        return [], warnings
 59
 60    def validate_sequential_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 61        errors = []
 62
 63        # 0. Check if the column exists
 64        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
 65        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 66        if not exists_column:
 67            return [msg_error_column], []
 68
 69        # Load the original codes and cleaned codes
 70        original_codes = pd.to_numeric(self._dataframe[column], errors="coerce")
 71        codes_cleaned = self._data_model.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE
 72
 73        # 1. Check if the column has only integers
 74        if original_codes.size != codes_cleaned.size:
 75            errors.append(
 76                f"{self._filename}: A verificação foi abortada porque a coluna '{column}' contém valores não numéricos."
 77            )
 78            return errors, []
 79
 80        # 2. Check if the first code is 1
 81        if codes_cleaned.at[0] != 1:
 82            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve começar em 1.")
 83
 84        # 3. Check if the codes are sequential and starting from 1
 85        if not codes_cleaned.equals(pd.Series(range(1, len(codes_cleaned) + 1))):
 86            errors.append(
 87                f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve conter valores inteiros e sequenciais (1, 2, 3, ...)."
 88            )
 89
 90        return errors, []
 91
 92    def validate_unique_codes(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 93        errors = []
 94        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
 95        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
 96        if not exists_column:
 97            return [msg_error_column], []
 98
 99        codes_cleaned = self._data_model.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE
100        duplicated_codes = codes_cleaned[codes_cleaned.duplicated()].tolist()
101
102        if duplicated_codes:
103            errors.append(
104                f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' contém códigos duplicados: {duplicated_codes}."
105            )
106
107        return errors, []
108
109    def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
110        warnings = []
111        columns_to_check = [
112            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
113            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
114        ]
115
116        for column in columns_to_check:
117            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
118            if not exists_column:
119                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
120                continue
121
122            # Filter non-empty values
123            mask = self._dataframe[column].notna() & (self._dataframe[column] != "")
124            filtered_data = self._dataframe[mask]
125
126            if not filtered_data.empty:
127                # Process original text with all replacements
128                original_series = (
129                    filtered_data[column]
130                    .astype(str)
131                    .str.replace("\r", "<CR>")
132                    .str.replace("\n", "<LF>")
133                    .str.replace("\x0d", "<CR>")
134                    .str.replace("\x0a", "<LF>")
135                )
136
137                # Process expected correct text with all replacements and capitalization
138                expected_series = (
139                    filtered_data[column]
140                    .astype(str)
141                    .str.replace("\x0d", "")
142                    .str.replace("\x0a", "")
143                    .str.strip()
144                    .apply(lambda x: capitalize_text_keep_acronyms(x.strip()))
145                )
146
147                # Find mismatches
148                mismatches_mask = original_series != expected_series
149                mismatches_indices = original_series[mismatches_mask].index
150
151                for idx in mismatches_indices:
152                    original_text = original_series.loc[idx]
153                    expected_text = expected_series.loc[idx]
154                    warnings.append(
155                        f"{self._filename}, linha {idx + 2}: Valor da coluna '{column}' fora do padrão. Esperado: '{expected_text}'. Encontrado: '{original_text}'."
156                    )
157
158        return [], warnings
159
160    def validate_indicator_levels(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
161        errors = []
162        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
163        exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
164        if not exists_column:
165            return [msg_error_column], []
166
167        for index, row in self._dataframe.iterrows():
168            level = row[column]
169            is_valid, __ = check_cell_integer(level, min_value=1)
170            if not is_valid:
171                line_updated = int(index) + 2
172                errors.append(
173                    f"{self._filename}, linha {line_updated}: O nível do indicador na coluna '{column}' deve ser um número inteiro maior que 0."
174                )
175        return errors, []

177    def validate_punctuation(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
178        warnings = []
179        columns_dont_punctuation = [
180            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
181            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
182        ]
183        columns_must_end_with_dot = [
184            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name,
185            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_DESC.name,
186        ]
187
188        for column in list(columns_dont_punctuation + columns_must_end_with_dot):
189            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
190            if not exists_column:
191                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
192
193        _, punctuation_warnings = check_punctuation(
194            self._dataframe,
195            self._filename,
196            columns_dont_punctuation,
197            columns_must_end_with_dot,
198        )
199        warnings.extend(punctuation_warnings)
200        return [], warnings

202    def validate_empty_strings(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
203        errors = []
204
205        columns_to_check = [
206            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
207            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
208            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name,
209            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_DESC.name,
210        ]
211        for column in columns_to_check:
212            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
213            if not exists_column:
214                errors.append(msg_error_column)
215                continue
216            empty_rows = self._dataframe[
217                self._dataframe[column].isna() | (self._dataframe[column] == "")
218            ].index
219            if not empty_rows.empty:
220                for index in empty_rows:
221                    errors.append(
222                        f"{self._filename}, linha {index + 2}: Nenhum item da coluna '{column}' pode ser vazio."
223                    )
224        return errors, []

226    def validate_cr_lf_characters(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
227        warnings = []
228
229        columns_start_end = self._data_model.EXPECTED_COLUMNS
230        columns_anywhere = [
231            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
232            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
233        ]
234
235        # Create an ordered dictionary with the columns
236        columns_to_check = list(
237            OrderedDict.fromkeys(columns_anywhere + columns_start_end).keys()
238        )
239
240        # Check if the columns exist
241        for column in columns_to_check:
242            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
243            if not exists_column:
244                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
245                continue
246
247        # Run the checks for CR/LF characters
248        __, all_warnings_cr_lf = check_special_characters_cr_lf(
249            self._dataframe, self._filename, columns_start_end, columns_anywhere
250        )
251
252        warnings.extend(all_warnings_cr_lf)
253        return [], warnings

255    def validate_title_length(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
256        """Validate the length of titles."""
257        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name
258        max_len = SpDescription.CONSTANTS.MAX_TITLE_LENGTH
259        return self._check_text_length(column, max_len)

261    def validate_simple_description_length(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
262        """Validate the length of simple descriptions."""
263        column = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_DESC.name
264        max_len = SpDescription.CONSTANTS.MAX_SIMPLE_DESC_LENGTH
265        return self._check_text_length(column, max_len)

270    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
271        """Runs all content validations for SpDescription."""
272        validations = [
273            (self.validate_html_in_descriptions, NamesEnum.HTML_DESC.value),
274            (self.validate_sequential_codes, NamesEnum.SC.value),
275            (self.validate_unique_codes, NamesEnum.CO_UN.value),
276            (self.validate_text_capitalization, NamesEnum.INP.value),
277            (self.validate_indicator_levels, NamesEnum.IL.value),
278            (self.validate_punctuation, NamesEnum.MAND_PUNC_DESC.value),
279            (self.validate_empty_strings, NamesEnum.EF.value),
280            (self.validate_cr_lf_characters, NamesEnum.LB_DESC.value),
281            (self.validate_simple_description_length, NamesEnum.SIMP_DESC_N.value),
282        ]
283        if self._dataframe.empty:
284            self.set_not_executed(validations)
285            return self._errors, self._warnings
286
287        # Add title length validation if the flag is not set to skip it
288        if not self._data_models_context.data_args.data_action.no_warning_titles_length:
289            validations.append((self.validate_title_length, NamesEnum.TITLES_N.value))
290
291        # BUILD REPORTS
292        self.build_reports(validations)
293
294        return self._errors, self._warnings

77            )
78            return errors, []
79
80        # 2. Check if the first code is 1
81        if codes_cleaned.at[0] != 1:
82            errors.append(f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve começar em 1.")
83
84        # 3. Check if the codes are sequential and starting from 1
85        if not codes_cleaned.equals(pd.Series(range(1, len(codes_cleaned) + 1))):
86            errors.append(
87                f"{self._filename}: A coluna '{column}' deve conter valores inteiros e sequenciais (1, 2, 3, ...)."
88            )
89
90        return errors, []

def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
109    def validate_text_capitalization(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
110        warnings = []
111        columns_to_check = [
112            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SIMPLE_NAME.name,
113            SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_COMPLETE_NAME.name,
114        ]
115
116        for column in columns_to_check:
117            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
118            if not exists_column:
119                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
120                continue
121
122            # Filter non-empty values
123            mask = self._dataframe[column].notna() & (self._dataframe[column] != "")
124            filtered_data = self._dataframe[mask]
125
126            if not filtered_data.empty:
127                # Process original text with all replacements
128                original_series = (
129                    filtered_data[column]
130                    .astype(str)
131                    .str.replace("\r", "<CR>")
132                    .str.replace("\n", "<LF>")
133                    .str.replace("\x0d", "<CR>")
134                    .str.replace("\x0a", "<LF>")
135                )
136
137                # Process expected correct text with all replacements and capitalization
138                expected_series = (
139                    filtered_data[column]
140                    .astype(str)
141                    .str.replace("\x0d", "")
142                    .str.replace("\x0a", "")
143                    .str.strip()
144                    .apply(lambda x: capitalize_text_keep_acronyms(x.strip()))
145                )
146
147                # Find mismatches
148                mismatches_mask = original_series != expected_series
149                mismatches_indices = original_series[mismatches_mask].index
150
151                for idx in mismatches_indices:
152                    original_text = original_series.loc[idx]
153                    expected_text = expected_series.loc[idx]
154                    warnings.append(
155                        f"{self._filename}, linha {idx + 2}: Valor da coluna '{column}' fora do padrão. Esperado: '{expected_text}'. Encontrado: '{original_text}'."
156                    )
157
158        return [], warnings

113    def validate_relation_indicators_in_values(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
114        """
115        Validate indicator relationships between values and descriptions.
116
117        Returns:
118            Tuple of (errors, warnings) lists
119        """
120        errors, warnings = [], []
121
122        if self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].empty:
123            return errors, warnings
124
125        errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
126            required_columns={
127                self.sp_name_description: self.global_required_columns[
128                    self.sp_name_description
129                ],
130                self.sp_name_scenario: self.global_required_columns[
131                    self.sp_name_scenario
132                ],
133            },
134            model_dataframes=self.model_dataframes,
135        )
136        if errors:
137            return errors, warnings
138
139        code_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
140        level_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
141        scenario_column_name = SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_SCENARIO.name
142
143        # Prepare cleaned dataframes
144        # No-need to clean the values dataframe
145        df_values = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_value].copy()
146        # Need to clean the description and temporal reference dataframes
147        df_description, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
148            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description],
149            self.sp_name_description,
150            [code_column_name],
151        )
152
153        level_one_codes = (
154            df_description[df_description[level_column_name] == "1"][code_column_name]
155            .astype(str)
156            .tolist()
157        )
158
159        # Process value columns
160        value_columns = df_values.columns.tolist()
161        columns_to_ignore = (
162            self.global_required_columns[self.sp_name_value] + level_one_codes
163        )
164
165        valid_value_codes, invalid_columns = (
166            extract_numeric_ids_and_unmatched_strings_from_list(
167                value_columns, columns_to_ignore, self.list_scenarios
168            )
169        )
170
171        # Filter out columns containing ':'
172        processed_invalid_columns = sorted(
173            {col for col in invalid_columns if ":" not in col}
174        )
175
176        if processed_invalid_columns:
177            errors.append(
178                f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: Colunas inválidas: {processed_invalid_columns}."
179            )
180
181        # Get filtered description codes using generic function
182        # Remove level 1 indicators
183        filtered_description_df = df_description[
184            df_description[level_column_name] != "1"
185        ].copy()
186
187        # Remove level 2 indicators with scenario 0 if scenario column exists
188        if (
189            self.exists_scenario
190            and scenario_column_name in filtered_description_df.columns
191        ):
192            filtered_description_df = filtered_description_df[
193                ~(
194                    (filtered_description_df[level_column_name] == "2")
195                    & (filtered_description_df[scenario_column_name] == "0")
196                )
197            ]
198
199        # Extract valid description codes
200        valid_description_codes, _ = extract_numeric_integer_ids_from_list(
201            id_values_list=set(filtered_description_df[code_column_name].astype(str))
202        )
203
204        # Compare codes between description and values
205        comparison_errors = find_differences_in_two_set_with_message(
206            first_set=valid_description_codes,
207            label_1=self.model_sp_description.filename,
208            second_set=valid_value_codes,
209            label_2=self.model_sp_value.filename,
210        )
211        errors.extend(comparison_errors)
212
213        return errors, warnings

215    def validate_value_combination_relation(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
216        """
217        Validate value combination relations between indicators and their expected columns.
218
219        This function ensures that each indicator has the correct combination of columns
220        in the values dataframe based on its level and scenario configuration.
221        """
222        errors, warnings = [], []
223
224        if (
225            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].empty
226            or self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_temporal_reference].empty
227        ):
228            return errors, warnings
229
230        code_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name
231        level_column_name = SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name
232        scenario_column_name = SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_SCENARIO.name
233        symbol_column_name = SpTemporalReference.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_SYMBOL.name
234
235        local_required_columns = self.global_required_columns.copy()
236        if self.exists_scenario:
237            local_required_columns[self.sp_name_description].append(
238                scenario_column_name
239            )
240
241        errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
242            required_columns=local_required_columns,
243            model_dataframes=self.model_dataframes,
244        )
245        if errors:
246            return errors, warnings
247
248        # Prepare cleaned dataframes
249        # No-need to clean the values dataframe
250        df_values = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_value].copy()
251
252        # Need to clean the description and temporal reference dataframes
253        df_description, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
254            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description],
255            self.sp_name_description,
256            local_required_columns[self.sp_name_description],
257        )
258        df_temporal_reference, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
259            self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_temporal_reference],
260            self.sp_name_temporal_reference,
261            local_required_columns[self.sp_name_temporal_reference],
262        )
263
264        # Get temporal symbols once (sorted for consistency)
265        temporal_symbols = sorted(df_temporal_reference[symbol_column_name].unique())
266        first_year = temporal_symbols[0]
267        sp_value_columns = set(df_values.columns)
268
269        # Process each indicator efficiently
270        for _, row in df_description.iterrows():
271            code = str(row[code_column_name])
272            level = int(row[level_column_name])
273            scenario = int(row[scenario_column_name]) if self.exists_scenario else 0
274
275            # Generate expected combinations based on level and scenario
276            expected_combinations = []
277            if level >= 2:
278                if scenario == 0:
279                    expected_combinations = [f"{code}-{first_year}"]
280                elif scenario == 1:
281                    expected_combinations = generate_combinations(
282                        code, first_year, temporal_symbols, self.list_scenarios
283                    )
284
285            # Validate required combinations exist
286            for combination in expected_combinations:
287                if combination not in sp_value_columns:
288                    # Skip validation for level 2 with scenario 0 (special case)
289                    if level == 2 and scenario == 0:
290                        continue
291                    errors.append(
292                        f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{combination}' é obrigatória."
293                    )
294
295            # Find actual combinations for this code
296            actual_combinations = [
297                col for col in sp_value_columns if col.startswith(f"{code}-")
298            ]
299
300            # Check for extra combinations
301            has_extra_error, extra_columns = find_extra_combinations(
302                expected_combinations, actual_combinations
303            )
304            if has_extra_error:
305                for extra_column in extra_columns:
306                    if level == 1:
307                        errors.append(
308                            f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{extra_column}' é desnecessária para o indicador de nível 1."
309                        )
310                    else:
311                        errors.append(
312                            f"{self.model_sp_value.filename}: A coluna '{extra_column}' é desnecessária."
313                        )
314
315        return errors, warnings

118    def validate_hierarchy_with_tree(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
119        """
120        Validate tree composition structure and detect cycles.
121
122        Returns:
123            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
124        """
125        errors: List[str] = []
126        warnings: List[str] = []
127
128        # Check required columns exist
129        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
130            self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes
131        )
132        if column_errors:
133            return column_errors, warnings
134
135        # Create working copies and clean data
136        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
137        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
138
139        # Clean integer columns: df_composition
140        df_composition, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
141            df=df_composition,
142            file_name=self.sp_name_composition,
143            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_parent],
144            min_value=0,
145        )
146        df_composition, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
147            df=df_composition,
148            file_name=self.sp_name_composition,
149            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_child],
150            min_value=1,
151        )
152
153        # Clean integer columns: df_description
154        df_description, _ = clean_dataframe_integers(
155            df=df_description,
156            file_name=self.sp_name_description,
157            columns_to_clean=[self.column_name_code, self.column_name_level],
158            min_value=1,
159        )
160
161        # Add root node if not present
162        if not (df_description[self.column_name_code] == 0).any():
163            root_row = pd.DataFrame(
164                [len(self.model_sp_description.EXPECTED_COLUMNS) * [0]],
165                columns=self.model_sp_description.EXPECTED_COLUMNS,
166            )
167            df_description = pd.concat([df_description, root_row], ignore_index=True)
168
169        # Build tree and check for cycles
170        tree = create_tree_structure(
171            df_composition, self.column_name_parent, self.column_name_child
172        )
173
174        cycle_found, cycle = detect_tree_cycles(tree)
175        if cycle_found:
176            errors.append(
177                f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Ciclo encontrado: [{' -> '.join(cycle)}]."
178            )
179
180        # Validate level composition
181        level_errors = validate_level_hierarchy(
182            df_composition,
183            df_description,
184            self.column_name_code,
185            self.column_name_level,
186            self.column_name_parent,
187            self.column_name_child,
188        )
189
190        errors.extend(
191            self._format_level_errors(level_errors, df_composition, df_description)
192        )
193
194        return errors, warnings
195
196    def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
197        """
198        Validate that all children of the same parent have the same level.
199
200        Returns:
201            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
202        """
203        errors: List[str] = []
204        warnings: List[str] = []
205
206        # Check required columns exist
207        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
208            self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes
209        )
210        if column_errors:
211            return column_errors, warnings
212
213        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
214        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
215
216        # Create level mapping
217        levels = {
218            row[self.column_name_code]: row[self.column_name_level]
219            for _, row in df_description.iterrows()
220        }
221
222        # Group by parent and validate children levels
223        parent_groups = df_composition.groupby(self.column_name_parent)
224        for parent, group in parent_groups:
225            if parent not in levels:
226                errors.append(
227                    f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Código pai {parent} não encontrado na descrição."
228                )
229                continue
230
231            children_info: List[Tuple[Any, Any]] = []
232
233            for _, row in group.iterrows():
234                child = row[self.column_name_child]
235                if child not in levels:
236                    errors.append(
237                        f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Código filho {child} não encontrado na descrição."
238                    )
239                    continue
240                child_level = levels[child]
241                children_info.append((child, child_level))
242
243            if children_info and len({level for _, level in children_info}) > 1:
244                error_children = ", ".join(
245                    [
246                        f"indicador {child} possui nível '{level}'"
247                        for child, level in children_info
248                    ]
249                )
250                errors.append(
251                    f"{self.sp_name_description}: Indicadores filhos do pai {parent} "
252                    f"não estão no mesmo nível: [{error_children}]."
253                )
254
255        return errors, warnings
256
257    def _format_level_errors(
258        self,
259        level_errors: List[Tuple[Any, Any]],
260        df_composition: pd.DataFrame,
261        df_description: pd.DataFrame,
262    ) -> List[str]:
263        """
264        Format level composition errors with proper line numbers and descriptions.
265
266        Args:
267            level_errors: List of (parent, child) error tuples
268            df_composition: Composition dataframe
269            df_description: Description dataframe
270
271        Returns:
272            List of formatted error messages
273        """
274        formatted_errors: List[str] = []
275
276        for parent, child in level_errors:
277            if parent is not None and child is not None:
278                # Find the row with this relationship
279                matching_rows = df_composition[
280                    (df_composition[self.column_name_parent] == int(parent))
281                    & (df_composition[self.column_name_child] == int(child))
282                ]
283
284                if not matching_rows.empty:
285                    row_index = matching_rows.index[0]
286                    line_number = row_index + 2
287
288                    parent_level = df_description[
289                        df_description[self.column_name_code] == int(parent)
290                    ][self.column_name_level].values[0]
291
292                    child_level = df_description[
293                        df_description[self.column_name_code] == int(child)
294                    ][self.column_name_level].values[0]
295
296                    formatted_errors.append(
297                        f"{self.sp_name_composition}, linha {line_number}: "
298                        f"O indicador {parent} (nível {parent_level}) não pode ser pai "
299                        f"do indicador {child} (nível {child_level}). "
300                        f"Atualize os níveis no arquivo de descrição."
301                    )
302
303        return formatted_errors

306        """
307        Execute all tree validation checks.
308
309        Returns:
310            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
311        """
312        validations = [
313            (self.validate_hierarchy_with_tree, NamesEnum.TH.value),

315        ]

317        if (
318            self.model_sp_composition.data_loader_model.df_data.empty
319            or self.model_sp_description.data_loader_model.df_data.empty
320        ):
321            self.set_not_executed(validations)
322            return self._errors, self._warnings
323
324        self.build_reports(validations)
325
326        return self._errors, self._warnings

162        if not (df_description[self.column_name_code] == 0).any():
163            root_row = pd.DataFrame(
164                [len(self.model_sp_description.EXPECTED_COLUMNS) * [0]],
165                columns=self.model_sp_description.EXPECTED_COLUMNS,
166            )
167            df_description = pd.concat([df_description, root_row], ignore_index=True)
168
169        # Build tree and check for cycles
170        tree = create_tree_structure(
171            df_composition, self.column_name_parent, self.column_name_child
172        )
173
174        cycle_found, cycle = detect_tree_cycles(tree)
175        if cycle_found:
176            errors.append(
177                f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Ciclo encontrado: [{' -> '.join(cycle)}]."
178            )
179
180        # Validate level composition
181        level_errors = validate_level_hierarchy(
182            df_composition,
183            df_description,
184            self.column_name_code,
185            self.column_name_level,
186            self.column_name_parent,
187            self.column_name_child,
188        )
189
190        errors.extend(
191            self._format_level_errors(level_errors, df_composition, df_description)
192        )
193
194        return errors, warnings

Validate tree composition structure and detect cycles.

Returns: Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists

def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
196    def validate_tree_levels_children(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
197        """
198        Validate that all children of the same parent have the same level.
199
200        Returns:
201            Tuple containing (errors, warnings) lists
202        """
203        errors: List[str] = []
204        warnings: List[str] = []
205
206        # Check required columns exist
207        column_errors = self.check_columns_in_models_dataframes(
208            self.global_required_columns, self.model_dataframes
209        )
210        if column_errors:
211            return column_errors, warnings
212
213        df_composition = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_composition].copy()
214        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
215
216        # Create level mapping
217        levels = {
218            row[self.column_name_code]: row[self.column_name_level]
219            for _, row in df_description.iterrows()
220        }
221
222        # Group by parent and validate children levels
223        parent_groups = df_composition.groupby(self.column_name_parent)
224        for parent, group in parent_groups:
225            if parent not in levels:
226                errors.append(
227                    f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Código pai {parent} não encontrado na descrição."
228                )
229                continue
230
231            children_info: List[Tuple[Any, Any]] = []
232
233            for _, row in group.iterrows():
234                child = row[self.column_name_child]
235                if child not in levels:
236                    errors.append(
237                        f"{self.sp_name_composition}: Código filho {child} não encontrado na descrição."
238                    )
239                    continue
240                child_level = levels[child]
241                children_info.append((child, child_level))
242
243            if children_info and len({level for _, level in children_info}) > 1:
244                error_children = ", ".join(
245                    [
246                        f"indicador {child} possui nível '{level}'"
247                        for child, level in children_info
248                    ]
249                )
250                errors.append(
251                    f"{self.sp_name_description}: Indicadores filhos do pai {parent} "
252                    f"não estão no mesmo nível: [{error_children}]."
253                )
254
255        return errors, warnings

Validate that all children of the same parent have the same level.

325
326        return self._errors, self._warnings

 85    def _prepare_statement(self):
 86        # Get model properties once
 87        self.sp_name_legend = self.model_sp_legend.filename
 88        self.sp_name_description = self.model_sp_description.filename
 89        self.sp_name_value = self.model_sp_value.filename
 90
 91        # Validate all required columns exist
 92        self.model_dataframes = {
 93            self.sp_name_legend: self.model_sp_legend.data_loader_model.df_data.copy(),
 94            self.sp_name_description: self.model_sp_description.data_loader_model.df_data.copy(),
 95            self.sp_name_value: self.model_sp_value.data_loader_model.df_data.copy(),
 96        }
 97
 98    def validate_relation_indicators_in_legend(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 99        errors, warnings = [], []
100
101        if not self.model_sp_legend.is_sanity_check_passed:
102            return errors, warnings
103
104        required_columns = {
105            self.sp_name_description: [
106                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name,
107                SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name,
108                SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name,
109            ]
110        }
111
112        for column in required_columns[self.sp_name_description]:
113            exists_column, msg_error = self.column_exists(
114                self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description],
115                self.sp_name_description,
116                column,
117            )
118            if not exists_column:
119                errors.append(msg_error)
120                break
121
122        if errors:
123            return errors, warnings
124
125        df_legend = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_legend].copy()
126        df_description = self.model_dataframes[self.sp_name_description].copy()
127
128        df_description_clean, __ = clean_dataframe_integers(
129            df_description,
130            self.sp_name_description,
131            [SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name],
132            min_value=1,
133        )
134
135        df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name] = (
136            pd.to_numeric(
137                df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name],
138                errors="coerce",
139            )
140        )
141        df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name] = (
142            df_description_clean[SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name].astype(
143                "Int64"
144            )
145        )
146
147        # Remove all NaN values in column COLUMN_LEGEND
148        df_description_clean = df_description_clean.dropna(
149            subset=[SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name]
150        )
151        df_legend = df_legend.dropna(subset=[SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name])
152
153        legends_id_in_description = (
154            df_description_clean[
155                (
156                    df_description_clean[SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name]
157                    != "1"
158                )
159                & (
160                    df_description_clean[
161                        SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name
162                    ].notna()
163                )
164                & (
165                    pd.to_numeric(
166                        df_description_clean[
167                            SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name
168                        ],
169                        errors="coerce",
170                    ).notna()
171                )
172            ][SpDescription.DynamicColumn.COLUMN_LEGEND.name]
173            .astype(str)
174            .tolist()
175        )  # DROP NA VALUES
176
177        legends_id_in_legend = (
178            df_legend[SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name]
179            .astype(str)
180            .unique()
181            .tolist()
182        )
183
184        set_one = set(legends_id_in_description)
185        set_two = set(legends_id_in_legend)
186
187        missing_in_b, missing_in_a = find_differences_in_two_set(
188            first_set=set_one,
189            second_set=set_two,
190        )
191
192        missing_in_b = {int(x) for x in missing_in_b if str(x).isdigit()}
193        missing_in_a = {int(x) for x in missing_in_a if str(x).isdigit()}
194
195        if missing_in_b:
196            errors.append(
197                f"{self.sp_name_description}: Códigos de legenda ausentes em {self.sp_name_legend}: {sorted(list(missing_in_b))}."
198            )
199
200        if missing_in_a:
201            warnings.append(
202                f"{self.sp_name_legend}: Códigos de legenda não referenciados em {self.sp_name_description}: {sorted(list(missing_in_a))}."
203            )
204
205        # 1. All codes that are level 1 - Cannot have legends: if they do, error
206
207        codes_indicators_level_one = (
208            df_description_clean[
209                df_description_clean[SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_LEVEL.name]
210                == "1"
211            ][SpDescription.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_CODE.name]
212            .astype(str)
213            .tolist()
214        )
215
216        legends_id_in_description_level_one = (
217            df_description_clean[
218                (

479    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
480        """Runs all content validations for SpLegend."""
481        validations = []
482
483        if self.model_sp_legend.is_sanity_check_passed:
484            validations.append(
485                (self.validate_relation_indicators_in_legend, NamesEnum.LEG_REL.value)
486            )
487        validations.append(
488            (self.validate_range_multiple_legend, NamesEnum.LEG_RANGE.value)
489        )
490
491        if self.model_sp_description.data_loader_model.df_data.empty:
492            self.set_not_executed(validations)
493            return self._errors, self._warnings
494
495        # BUILD REPORTS
496        self.build_reports(validations)
497
498        return self._errors, self._warnings

419                        group_legend[SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_MINIMUM.name] = (
420                            pd.to_numeric(
421                                group_legend[
422                                    SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_MINIMUM.name
423                                ],
424                                errors="coerce",
425                            )
426                        )
427                        group_legend[SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_MAXIMUM.name] = (
428                            pd.to_numeric(
429                                group_legend[
430                                    SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_MAXIMUM.name
431                                ],
432                                errors="coerce",
433                            )
434                        )
435
436                        aux_min_value = group_legend[
437                            SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_MINIMUM.name
438                        ].min()
439                        aux_max_value = group_legend[
440                            SpLegend.RequiredColumn.COLUMN_MAXIMUM.name
441                        ].max()
442
443                        if not pd.isna(aux_min_value) and not pd.isna(aux_max_value):
444                            aux_data_mapping_legend.min_value = aux_min_value
445                            aux_data_mapping_legend.max_value = aux_max_value
446
447            mapping_legends[data_column_sp_value] = aux_data_mapping_legend
448
449        df_values_numeric = df_values.copy()
450        for col in valid_columns_from_values:
451            df_values_numeric[col] = pd.to_numeric(
452                df_values[col].astype(str).str.replace(",", "."), errors="coerce"
453            )
454
455        for data_column_sp_value in valid_columns_from_values:
456            code_column = data_column_sp_value.split("-")[0]
457
458            if code_column in codes_indicators_level_one:
459                continue
460
461            min_value = mapping_legends[data_column_sp_value].min_value
462            max_value = mapping_legends[data_column_sp_value].max_value
463
464            for index, value_numeric in df_values_numeric[data_column_sp_value].items():
465                value_original = df_values[data_column_sp_value][index]
466                if (
467                    value_original == self._data_models_context.config.VALUE_DI
468                    or pd.isna(value_numeric)
469                ):
470                    continue
471
472                if value_numeric < min_value or value_numeric > max_value:
473                    errors.append(
474                        f"{self.sp_name_value}, linha {index + 2}: O valor {value_original} está fora do intervalo da legenda ({min_value} a {max_value}) para a coluna '{data_column_sp_value}'."
475                    )
476
477        return errors, warnings

 72    def validate_spellchecker(
 73        self, model_class: Type[Union[SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario]]
 74    ) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
 75        """
 76        Generic spellchecker validation method that works with any model class.
 77
 78        Args:
 79            model_class: The model class to validate (e.g., SpDescription, SpTemporalReference, SpScenario)
 80
 81        Returns:
 82            Tuple containing lists of errors and warnings
 83        """
 84        errors, warnings = [], []
 85
 86        # Configure local instances
 87        self._data_model = self._data_models_context.get_instance_of(model_class)
 88        self._dataframe = self._data_model.data_loader_model.df_data.copy()
 89        self._filename = self._data_model.filename
 90
 91        if self._dataframe.empty:
 92            return errors, warnings
 93
 94        # Get columns to check for this model
 95        columns_to_check = self.model_columns_map.get(model_class, [])
 96
 97        if not columns_to_check:
 98            # If no columns defined for this model, skip validation
 99            return errors, warnings
100
101        # Check if the columns exist
102        for column in columns_to_check:
103            exists_column, msg_error_column = self._column_exists(column)
104            if not exists_column:
105                warnings.append(msg_error_column)
106                continue
107
108        # Perform spellcheck
109        errors_spellchecker, warnings_spellchecker = (
110            self.spellchecker.check_spelling_text(
111                df=self._dataframe,
112                file_name=self._filename,
113                columns_sheets=columns_to_check,
114            )
115        )
116
117        errors.extend(errors_spellchecker)
118        warnings.extend(warnings_spellchecker)
119
120        return errors, warnings
121
122    def _prepare_statement(self):
123        if self.spellchecker.errors_dictionary:
124            self._errors.extend(self.spellchecker.errors_dictionary)
125
126    def run(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
127        """Runs all content validations for SpScenario."""
128
129        validations = []
130        if not self._data_models_context.data_args.data_action.no_spellchecker:
131            # Add validation for Description
132            validations.append(
133                (
134                    lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpDescription),
135                    NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
136                )
137            )
138
139            # Add validation for Temporal Reference
140            validations.append(
141                (
142                    lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpTemporalReference),
143                    NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
144                )
145            )
146
147            # Add validation for Scenario if scenarios exist
148            if self._data_model.scenarios_list:
149                validations.append(
150                    (
151                        lambda: self.validate_spellchecker(SpScenario),
152                        NamesEnum.SPELL.value,
153                    )
154                )
155
156        # BUILD REPORTS
157        self.build_reports(validations)
158
159        # Cleanup temporary files
160        self.spellchecker.clean_files_generated()
161
162        return self._errors, self._warnings

 81    def check_not_expected_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
 82        """
 83        Check for unexpected folders or files in the input directory.
 84        """
 85        local_errors = []
 86        expected_files = self.context.config.EXPECTED_FILES
 87        optional_files = self.context.config.OPTIONAL_FILES
 88
 89        if len(self.dir_files) == 1:
 90            dir_path = os.path.join(
 91                self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, self.dir_files[0]
 92            )
 93            is_dir, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_directory_exists(dir_path)
 94            if is_dir:
 95                local_errors.append(
 96                    self.context.lm.text(
 97                        "validator_structure_error_files_not_in_folder"
 98                    )
 99                )
100                return not local_errors, local_errors
101
102        for file_name in self.dir_files:
103            file_path = os.path.join(
104                self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, file_name
105            )
106            is_file, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_file_exists(file_path)
107            if not is_file:
108                local_errors.append(
109                    self.context.lm.text(
110                        "validator_structure_error_unexpected_folder"
111                    ).format(file_name=file_name)
112                )
113                continue
114
115            file_base, file_ext = os.path.splitext(file_name)
116            if file_base in expected_files and file_ext in expected_files[file_base]:
117                continue
118            if file_base in optional_files and file_ext in optional_files[file_base]:
119                continue
120
121            local_errors.append(
122                self.context.lm.text(
123                    "validator_structure_error_unexpected_file"
124                ).format(file_name=file_name)
125            )
126
127        return not local_errors, local_errors

129    def check_expected_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
130        """
131        Check if all expected files are present in the input directory.
132        """
133        local_errors = []
134        expected_files = self.context.config.EXPECTED_FILES
135
136        for file_base, extensions in expected_files.items():
137            file_found = False
138            for ext in extensions:
139                file_path = os.path.join(
140                    self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, f"{file_base}{ext}"
141                )
142                is_file, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_file_exists(file_path)
143                if is_file:

145                    break
146            if not file_found:
147                local_errors.append(
148                    self.context.lm.text(
149                        "validator_structure_error_missing_file"
150                    ).format(file_base=file_base)
151                )
152        return not local_errors, local_errors

154    def check_ignored_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
155        """
156        Check for files that will be ignored in the root folder.
157        Emit an error if both .xlsx and .csv files with the same name exist.
158        """
159        local_errors = []
160        file_groups = {}
161
162        for file_name in self.dir_files:
163            file_base, file_ext = os.path.splitext(file_name)
164            if file_ext in [".xlsx", ".csv"]:
165                if file_base not in file_groups:
166                    file_groups[file_base] = []
167                file_groups[file_base].append(file_ext)
168
169        for file_base, extensions in file_groups.items():
170            if ".xlsx" in extensions and ".csv" in extensions:
171                local_errors.append(
172                    self.context.lm.text(
173                        "validator_structure_error_conflicting_files"
174                    ).format(file_base=file_base)
175                )
176
177        return not local_errors, local_errors

179    def validate_all_general_structure(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
180        """
181        Perform all validation checks on the input folder.
182
183        Returns:
184            List[str]: A list of validation errors.
185        """
186        all_errors = [
187            [self.check_empty_directory()],
188            [self.check_not_expected_files_in_folder_root()],
189            [self.check_expected_files_in_folder_root()],
190            [self.check_ignored_files_in_folder_root()],
191        ]
192        for check in all_errors:
193            is_valid, errors = check[0]
194            if not is_valid:
195                self.errors.extend(errors)
196
197        return self.errors, []

200        """Runs all content validations for SpValue."""

204        ]

137            file_found = False
138            for ext in extensions:
139                file_path = os.path.join(
140                    self.context.data_args.data_file.input_folder, f"{file_base}{ext}"
141                )
142                is_file, _ = self.context.fs_utils.check_file_exists(file_path)
143                if is_file:
144                    file_found = True
145                    break
146            if not file_found:
147                local_errors.append(
148                    self.context.lm.text(
149                        "validator_structure_error_missing_file"
150                    ).format(file_base=file_base)
151                )
152        return not local_errors, local_errors

Check if all expected files are present in the input directory.

def check_ignored_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, typing.List[str]]: 
154    def check_ignored_files_in_folder_root(self) -> tuple[bool, List[str]]:
155        """
156        Check for files that will be ignored in the root folder.
157        Emit an error if both .xlsx and .csv files with the same name exist.
158        """
159        local_errors = []
160        file_groups = {}
161
162        for file_name in self.dir_files:
163            file_base, file_ext = os.path.splitext(file_name)
164            if file_ext in [".xlsx", ".csv"]:
165                if file_base not in file_groups:
166                    file_groups[file_base] = []
167                file_groups[file_base].append(file_ext)
168
169        for file_base, extensions in file_groups.items():
170            if ".xlsx" in extensions and ".csv" in extensions:
171                local_errors.append(
172                    self.context.lm.text(
173                        "validator_structure_error_conflicting_files"
174                    ).format(file_base=file_base)
175                )
176
177        return not local_errors, local_errors

Check for files that will be ignored in the root folder. Emit an error if both .xlsx and .csv files with the same name exist.

def validate_all_general_structure(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]: 
179    def validate_all_general_structure(self) -> Tuple[List[str], List[str]]:
180        """
181        Perform all validation checks on the input folder.
182
183        Returns:
184            List[str]: A list of validation errors.
185        """
186        all_errors = [
187            [self.check_empty_directory()],
188            [self.check_not_expected_files_in_folder_root()],
189            [self.check_expected_files_in_folder_root()],
190            [self.check_ignored_files_in_folder_root()],
191        ]
192        for check in all_errors:
193            is_valid, errors = check[0]
194            if not is_valid:
195                self.errors.extend(errors)
196
197        return self.errors, []
